<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">NN is one of the most prolific double-consonant pairs in Scrabble. With 6 N tiles in the bag — more than any other consonant except R — you will draw N pairs frequently. The -NNING pattern alone produces dozens of playable bingos (RUNNING, WINNING, SPINNING), and shorter NN words like INN, ANN, and PENNANT provide reliable gap-fillers throughout the game.</p>

